Package be.kuleuven.micas.signalStorage.formats.psfAscii

Class Summary
HeaderPsfAscii A helper class to read the header of a HSPICE Ascii file and construct a corresponding SimulationOutputHeader startOfData indicates the value of the first data-point, so little time is lost by splitting the reading procedure in two parts To output this file format in spectre, add these lines to the spice netlist: option1 options rawfmt = psfascii ("option1" is the name of the simulation and can be anything you like)
PsfAsciiLineReader helper class that allows to read ascii-files line-by-line It is specifically meant for reading psfAscii files as it treats PROP( .....
SimulationPsfAscii  
SimulationPsfAsciiDC psfAscii for a file with a single DC point instead of tran / dc sweep example format: VALUE "in" "V" 0.150000 "out" "V" 0.00498712 "Vin:p" "I" -2.91363e-12 "Vvdd:p" "I" -1.62174e-08 "Vvss:p" "I" 1.62204e-08 "vdd" "V" 0.150000 "vss" "V" 0.00000
